Package oogasalad.fileparser

Class GameObjectDataParser

java.lang.Object
oogasalad.fileparser.GameObjectDataParser
public class GameObjectDataParser extends Object
Responsible for parsing an XML element representing game objects into a list of GameObjectData records.

This parser extracts blueprint IDs, coordinates, and UUIDs for each game object instance described in the XML element. It is used to reconstruct level objects from structured XML data.

Author:
Billy McCune

  • Method Details

    • getGameObjectData

      public List<GameObjectData> getGameObjectData(Element gameObjectElement, int z) throws GameObjectParseException
      Parses a game object XML element and creates a list of GameObjectData records.

      The method reads the blueprint ID, a list of UUIDs, and a coordinate string of the form "(x1,y1),(x2,y2),...". Each UUID is paired with one coordinate set to form a GameObjectData entry.

      Parameters:
      gameObjectElement - the XML element representing the game object
      z - the z-index layer of the game object
      Returns:
      a list of GameObjectData objects created from the element
      Throws:
      GameObjectParseException - if the input data is malformed or parsing fails
